FBIS4-14747 "drsov064_f_94033" FBIS-SOV-94-064 Daily Report 4 Apr 1994 National Affairs Uranium Industry Lacks Safety Controls Uranium Industry Lacks Safety Controls LD0404104894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0949 GMT 4 Apr 94 LD0404104894 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Nekrasova] [Text] Lvov April 4 TASS -- The situation in the uranium industry is not controlled by anybody, said Konstantin Rudya, head of the national department for nuclear and radiation safety at the Ministry for Environmental Protection, after the end of his inspection trip to a number of uranium producing enterprises in Zheltiy Vodiy, Dnepropetrovsk region. He stressed that the extraction and processing of uranium were control-free in the region. Sanitary control authorities are not given the needed information, and there is no normative base in that sphere.
